\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ year of Ahaz. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ and she shall call his name\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  Divine inspiration will rest upon her. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ Immanuel\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  [lit. God is 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ with us. That is] to say that our Rock shall be with us, and this is the sign, for she is a young girl, and 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ she never prophesied, yet in this instance, Divine inspiration shall rest upon her. This is what is stated 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ below (8:3): “And I was intimate with the prophetess, etc.,” and we do not find a prophet’s wife called 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ a prophetess unless she prophesied. Some interpret this as being said about Hezekiah, but it is 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ impossible, because, when you count his years, you find that Hezekiah was born nine years before his 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ father’s reign. And some interpret that this is the sign, that she was a young girl and incapable of giving 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ birth.  
